therapeutic movement 

first a passing of my family, now a passing of the dance community. everything just feels heavy rn. i pray for all. 

learning a lot about grief this year. the first bit was so hard to realize life keeps going although it feels like yours just stopped. there’s a deep sadness that lives under all the other emotions at all times. next, it hits so randomly. one day you’ll wake up and you’ll feel physical pain in your heart, one day it slowly rises and consumes your thoughts, one day it will be triggered by a specific sense. it’s unpredictable but i like to believe those times where it’s heavily in the forefront of your heart are when that spirit is truly right there with you, hugging you & holding you.

This past week——went off the grid. 

Celebrated a New Year for growth and abundance. 
+
Celebrated 2 years of healthy love. 

Very very grateful <3

lately <3

lil story for #2: 
a year and 5 months ago my car was broken into and stolen (along with everything inside), then found in an alley for me to have to fix up and handle myself as my insurance didn’t cover anything.

two weeks after that, my identity was stolen, along with everything in my bank account. after lots of trouble, claims, police reports, and freezing accounts/credit i was able to get money back, but not my comfort and security. 

i recently purchased a brand new car all on my own. ngl i’ve worked really hard to get here. grateful 🙏
